252.9	Hydrogen	Hydrogen	Hydrogen ( -dr…ô-jin) is the chemical element with atomic number 1. It is represented by the symbol H. With an average atomic weight of 4 u (25 u for hydrogen-1), hydrogen is the lightest and most abundant chemical element, constituting roughly 75% of the Universe's chemical elemental mass. Non-remnant stars are mainly composed of hydrogen in its plasma state. Naturally occurring elemental hydrogen is relatively rare on Earth.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Hydrogen_discharge_tube.jpg/250px-Hydrogen_discharge_tube.jpg
